public class EnumProperty<T extends Enum<T> & StringIdentifiable> extends Property<T>
Represents a property that has enum values.

Notes on the enum class:

  • The enum class is required to have 2 or more values.
  • The enum class is required to provide a name for each value by overriding StringIdentifiable.asString().
  • The names of the values are required to match the valid name pattern. Otherwise, IllegalArgumentException will be thrown during the validation of a property.

See Properties for example usages.
